==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Consectary
<hw>Con"sec*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>consectarius</ets>, fr. <ets>consectari</ets> to follow after
eagerly; <ets>con-</ets> + <ets>sectari</ets> to follow eagerly, fr.
<ets>sequi</ets> to follow.]</ety> <def>Following by consequence;
consequent; deducible.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Consectary</xex> impieties.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consectary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Consectary
<hw>Con"sec*ta*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which follows by
consequence or is logically deducible; deduction from premises;
corollary.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consecute</ent>⟦br⟧
